  "description": "FCC converts heavy gas oil to gasoline (45-60% yield) and propylene using zeolite Y catalyst at 500-550°C. Hydrocracking converts VGO to diesel and jet fuel at 350-430°C and 80-200 bar with hydrogen. Reforming produces BTX aromatics and hydrogen from naphtha at 490-530°C over Pt-Re catalyst.",
